Problem:
Minimize XOR

------------------------------------------------------------

Statement:
Given two positive integers num1 and num2, find the positive integer x such that:

• x has the same number of set bits as num2  
• The value (x XOR num1) is minimal  

Return the integer x.  
The test cases are generated such that x is uniquely determined.

------------------------------------------------------------

Key Definitions:
• XOR (^) → bitwise XOR operation  
• Set bits → number of 1s in binary representation  

------------------------------------------------------------

Examples:

Example 1:
Input:  num1 = 3, num2 = 5  
Output: 3  

Binary:
num1 = 0011  
num2 = 0101  

x = 3 has same number of set bits as num2  
3 XOR 3 = 0 (minimum possible)

------------------------------------------------------------

Example 2:
Input:  num1 = 1, num2 = 12  
Output: 3  

Binary:
num1 = 0001  
num2 = 1100  

x = 3 has same number of set bits as num2  
3 XOR 1 = 2 (minimum)

------------------------------------------------------------

Constraints:
1 <= num1, num2 <= 10^9

------------------------------------------------------------

Code:

class Solution {
public:
    void setBit(int &x, int bit) {
        x |= (1 << bit);
    }

    bool isSet(int x, int bit) {
        return (x & (1 << bit)) != 0;
    }

    bool isUnset(int x, int bit) {
        return (x & (1 << bit)) == 0;
    }

    int minimizeXor(int num1, int num2) {
        int x = 0;
        int requiredSetBitCount = __builtin_popcount(num2);

        for (int bit = 31; bit >= 0 && requiredSetBitCount > 0; bit--) {
            if (isSet(num1, bit)) {
                setBit(x, bit);
                requiredSetBitCount--;
            }
        }

        for (int bit = 0; bit < 32 && requiredSetBitCount > 0; bit++) {
            if (isUnset(x, bit)) {
                setBit(x, bit);
                requiredSetBitCount--;
            }
        }

        return x;
    }
};

------------------------------------------------------------

Core Intuition (Easy to Revise ⭐):

• XOR value is minimized when higher bits match  
• First, copy highest set bits from num1 into x  
• This reduces XOR the most  
• If more bits are required, fill remaining bits from lowest positions  
• Total set bits in x must equal popcount(num2)

------------------------------------------------------------

Why Two Loops?

Loop 1 (31 → 0):
• Prioritizes higher bits  
• Minimizes XOR effectively  

Loop 2 (0 → 31):
• Completes remaining required set bits  
• Ensures exact popcount match  

------------------------------------------------------------

Time Complexity:
O(32) → O(1)

Space Complexity:
O(1)

------------------------------------------------------------
